procedureJavascriptCode.code:
/* ATR Based Grid */

// The ATR Based Grid allows to create a grid considering the current Average True Range. By setting an upper and lower ATR based limit from candle.close,
// and splitting the total range between min and max, into a given number of grid lines.

let candle = record.current

// Remember that you might have to change the number of records if you choose to use a different variable.totalGrids
variable.atrPeriod = 14 // The default value for ATR is 14
variable.atrAbove = 2 // Number of ATRs above candle.close - This will represent the top grid line
variable.atrBelow = 2 // Number of ATRs below candle.close - This will represent the bottom gridline
variable.totalGrids = 21 // Number of grids, including the top and bottom

let range = candle.max - candle.min
variable.savedRange.push(range)
if (variable.savedRange.length > variable.atrPeriod) {
    variable.savedRange.splice(0,1)
}
variable.atr = variable.savedRange.reduce((a,b) => a+b,0) / variable.savedRange.length

let borderMax = candle.close + (variable.atr * variable.atrAbove)
let borderMin = candle.close - (variable.atr * variable.atrBelow)
let spacing = (borderMax - borderMin) / variable.totalGrids

// Create the variable.arr from the bottom to top, setting a grid line with a given spacing.
variable.arr.length = 0
for (i=0; i<variable.totalGrids; i++) {
    let value = 0

    if (i === 0) {
        value = borderMin
        variable.arr.push(value)
    }
    else {
        value = variable.arr[i-1] + spacing
        variable.arr.push(value)
    }
}

variable.grid0 = Math.min(...variable.arr)   // Bottom border
variable.grid1 = variable.arr[1]
variable.grid2 = variable.arr[2]
variable.grid3 = variable.arr[3]
variable.grid4 = variable.arr[4]
variable.grid5 = variable.arr[5]
variable.grid6 = variable.arr[6]
variable.grid7 = variable.arr[7]
variable.grid8 = variable.arr[8]
variable.grid9 = variable.arr[9]
variable.grid10 = variable.arr[10]           // Mid-line
variable.grid11 = variable.arr[11]
variable.grid12 = variable.arr[12]
variable.grid13 = variable.arr[13]
variable.grid14 = variable.arr[14]
variable.grid15 = variable.arr[15]
variable.grid16 = variable.arr[16]
variable.grid17 = variable.arr[17]
variable.grid18 = variable.arr[18]
variable.grid19 = variable.arr[19]
variable.grid20 = Math.max(...variable.arr)  // Top border

variable.gridRange = (spacing / candle.close) * 100

// Happy trading! CJ.

/* Bollinger Bands Grid */

let candle = record.current
let hlc3 = (candle.max + candle.min + candle.close) / 3

variable.bbPeriod = 20
variable.deviation = 2
variable.totalGrids = 21

variable.savedClose.push(candle.close)
if (variable.savedClose.length > variable.bbPeriod) {
    variable.savedClose.splice(0,1)
}

variable.savedHlc3.push(hlc3)
if (variable.savedHlc3.length > variable.bbPeriod) {
    variable.savedHlc3.splice(0,1)
}

stdDeviation = getStdDeviation(variable.savedClose, variable.savedHlc3)
smaClose = variable.savedClose.reduce((a,b) => a+b,0) / variable.savedClose.length

upperBand = smaClose + (stdDeviation * variable.deviation)
lowerBand = smaClose - (stdDeviation * variable.deviation)

let borderMax = upperBand
let borderMin = lowerBand
let spacing = (borderMax - borderMin) / variable.totalGrids

// Create the variable.arr from the bottom to top, setting a grid line with a given spacing.
variable.arr.length = 0
for (i=0; i<variable.totalGrids; i++) {
    let value = 0

    if (i === 0) {
        value = borderMin
        variable.arr.push(value)
    }
    else {
        value = variable.arr[i-1] + spacing
        variable.arr.push(value)
    }
}

variable.grid0 = Math.min(...variable.arr)   // Bottom border
variable.grid1 = variable.arr[1]
variable.grid2 = variable.arr[2]
variable.grid3 = variable.arr[3]
variable.grid4 = variable.arr[4]
variable.grid5 = variable.arr[5]
variable.grid6 = variable.arr[6]
variable.grid7 = variable.arr[7]
variable.grid8 = variable.arr[8]
variable.grid9 = variable.arr[9]
variable.grid10 = variable.arr[10]           // Mid-line
variable.grid11 = variable.arr[11]
variable.grid12 = variable.arr[12]
variable.grid13 = variable.arr[13]
variable.grid14 = variable.arr[14]
variable.grid15 = variable.arr[15]
variable.grid16 = variable.arr[16]
variable.grid17 = variable.arr[17]
variable.grid18 = variable.arr[18]
variable.grid19 = variable.arr[19]
variable.grid20 = Math.max(...variable.arr)  // Top border

variable.gridRange = (spacing / candle.close) * 100

// Happy trading! CJ.

function getStdDeviation(close, typPrice) {
    let array = []
    array.length = 0

    smaTypPrice = typPrice.reduce((a,b) => a+b,0) / typPrice.length

    for (i=0; i<close.length; i++) {
        deviationValue = Math.pow((close[i] - smaTypPrice),2)
        array.push(deviationValue)
    }

    stdDeviation = Math.sqrt(array.reduce((a,b) => a+b,0) / (close.length-1))
    return stdDeviation
}
